 »magischen Denken« führen.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aArt and society. 0aCreative ability. 4aAffekt. 4aBildungsprozesse. 4aCultural Studies. 4aFélix Guattari. 4aGilles Deleuze. 4aHoward Becker. 4aJacques Rancière. 4aKultur. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aKunst. 4aKunstsoziologie. 4aKunsttheorie. 4aMedien. 4aNicolas Bourriaud. 4aPerformativität. 4aPierre Bourdieu. 4aProzessphilosophie. 4aRaymond Williams. 4aTheater. 4aUmberto Eco. 4aÄsthetik. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh  aAesthetics.  aAffect.  aArt.  aCultural Studies.  aCulture.  aEducation Processes.  aFélix Guattari.  aGilles Deleuze.  aHoward Becker.  aJacques Rancière.  aMedia.  aNicolas Bourriaud.  aPerformativity.  aPierre Bourdieu.  aProcess Philosophy.  aRaymond Williams.  aSociology of Art.  aTheatre.  aTheory of Art.  aUmberto Eco.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2020z9783111025124oZDB-23-TGP0 cprintz978383765325040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839453254?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839453254423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839453254/original  a978-3-11-069629-5  DG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2b2020  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-SEWb2020  aZDB-23-TGPb2020